postcontent: For sale or trade is this great Wiley Clapp special edition Ruger GP100 in 38/357. I am the first owner of this beautiful yet rugged firearm, and it has served me well as a nightstand gun for the past two years. Total it probably hasn’t had much more than 200 rounds through it, and the vast majority of those were .38s. The only reason I changed it out is because it was a little big for my wife’s small hands, and I want to make sure she has something she is comfortable using if I am away. The matte stainless finish is attractive and practical and exhibits only minor wear from the drawer and range trips. The grips really make it stand out from your average run of the mill revolver, with the very nice rubber grips with checkered wood inserts. It is really the best of both worlds here, with the shock absorbing properties of the rubber with the great style and and grippiness of the checkered wood. I would prefer to meet at either Mechanicsburg Ordnance or SPAR Firearms to do the transfer, but am open to anywhere reasonable within the Mechanicsburg, Carlisle, Camp Hill area.
